her-order calculations.\n  Finally, renormalization group equations are derived within this framework,\nand the derivation is compared with the more customary calculation in the\ncontext of symmetry-invariant regularizations. We explain why, at one-loop\nlevel, the extra BMHV-specific counterterms do not change the results for the\nRGE. The results we find complete those that have been obtained previously in\nthe literature in the absence of scalar fields.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 29 Apr 2020 18:00:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 20 May 2020 23:53:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-08-26"}
