g\nand blow-up formulae. This agreement suggests that i) generating functions of\nDT invariants for a large class of quivers coming from strong exceptional\ncollections are mock modular functions of higher depth and ii) non-trivial\nsingle-centered black holes and scaling solutions do not exist quantum\nmechanically in such local Calabi-Yau geometries.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 29 Apr 2020 20:41:25 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 10 Jun 2020 17:21:58 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 13 Jul 2020 08:49:21 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 3 May 2021 16:03:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-30"}
